In this article, President Biden is seen meeting with the House and Senate leadership in the Oval Office. The President emphasizes his goal of being a President for all Americans and discusses the need to reach a compromise on infrastructure. He expresses his hope that a consensus can be reached and that the meeting will focus on finding a compromise that gets the people's work done and is agreeable to everyone. When asked how he expects to achieve this, the President jokes that he can simply snap his fingers to make it happen.